com.microsoft - LambOptimizer#

  • LambOptimizer - 1

LambOptimizer - 1#

Version

  • name: LambOptimizer (GitHub)

  • domain: com.microsoft

  • since_version: 1

  • function:

  • support_level: SupportType.COMMON

  • shape inference: True

This version of the operator has been available since version 1 of domain com.microsoft.

Summary

Attributes

  • alpha - FLOATS : Coefficient of previous gradient in running average.

  • beta - FLOATS : Coefficient of previous squared gradient in running average.The effective learning rate is computed by r = R / (1 + T * decay_factor). Default to 0 so that increasing update counts doesnt reduce the learning rate.

  • do_bias_correction - INT : Compute unbiased 1st and 2nd momentums.

  • epsilon - FLOATS : Small scalar to avoid dividing by zero.

  • lambda - FLOATS : Regularization coefficient of 0.5 * lambda * ||X||_2^2. Default to 0, which means no regularization.

  • max_norm_clip - FLOATS : clip threshold of gradients.

  • ratio_max - FLOAT : Upper bound on confidence ratio.

  • ratio_min - FLOAT : Lower bound on confidence ratio.

Inputs

Between 0 and 5125 inputs.

  • update_signal (optional, heterogeneous) - T_BOOL:

  • loss_scale (optional, heterogeneous) - T2:

  • gradient_norm (optional, heterogeneous) - T_GRAD_NORM:

Type Constraints

  • T1 in ( tensor(bfloat16), tensor(double), tensor(float), tensor(float16) ): Constrain input types to float scalars.

  • T2 in ( tensor(double), tensor(float) ): Constrain input types to float tensors.

  • T3 in ( tensor(bfloat16), tensor(double), tensor(float), tensor(float16) ): Constrain input types to float tensors.

  • T4 in ( tensor(bfloat16), tensor(double), tensor(float), tensor(float16) ): Constrain input types to float tensors.

  • T_MIXED_PRECISION_FP in ( tensor(bfloat16), tensor(float16) ): Constrain input types to float16 or bfloat16 tensors.

  • T_GRAD_NORM in ( tensor(bfloat16), tensor(double), tensor(float), tensor(float16) ): Constrain input types to float tensors.

  • T_BOOL in ( tensor(bool) ): Constrain types to boolean tensors.

  • TInt64 in ( tensor(int64) ): Constrain update count to 64-bit integer
